    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.41) and **Trea Turner** (70.46) serving as the clear offensive anchors. **Yordan Alvarez** draws a favorable matchup against Cecconi, where his elite xwOBA of 0.393 and a prime #2 spot in the order justify his position as the highest-scoring play of the day. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** remains an essential start; despite a slight discount for Rea\u2019s ability to hold runners, **Trea Turner**'s #1 lineup placement and aggressive base-running upside in a 5x5 Roto format make him nearly impossible to sit. **Kyle Schwarber** (69.69) rounds out the top tier, benefiting significantly from a favorable park factor and an elite xwOBA that maximizes his power-hitting floor.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision involved **Dillon Dingler**, who posted a 36.10, falling just below our established 40.0 efficiency threshold. While **Dillon Dingler** benefited from park factors against Gray, his platoon disadvantage and spot in the batting order limited his upside compared to our active infielders. Elsewhere, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (60.49) remains a high-upside play; while he faces an elite catcher in Nola, his massive 14% platoon edge keeps him firmly in the lineup. Conversely, **Victor Scott II** (43.78) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (45.64) are hanging on to marginal status; **Victor Scott II** in particular suffers from a late-order batting position that threatens his efficiency despite his necessity for stolen base coverage. \n\nWe are monitoring **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Luke Raley** closely for potential mid-game defensive substitutions, as both are navigating tough defensive matchups against elite arms. We are currently without **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Carson Benge** due to injury or scheduling, leaving our depth restricted. While we have bench coverage from **Gary Sanchez**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Josh Smith**, **Chase Meidroth**, and **Luis Pena**, no bench options currently project to surpass the efficiency scores of our starters.",
